Ryazan, or Рязань as the locals insist on writing it, isn't some fleeting trend. It’s a city that’s been around, a solid fixture on the map of [Central Russia](/Central_Russia). Nestled by the [Oka River](/Oka_River), it sits 196 kilometers southeast of the ever-present shadow of [Moscow](/Moscow). In 2010, it housed a population of 524,927 souls, making it the [33rd most populous city in Russia](/List_of_cities_and_towns_in_Russia_by_population). It’s a respectable number, enough to keep things interesting, but not so many that it’s drowning in its own sprawl.

